  "headline": "Renaissance Art",
  "description": "Renaissance art (14th-16th centuries, Italy) revolutionized Western art through: linear perspective (Brunelleschi, ~1415), anatomical accuracy, chiaroscuro (light/shadow), sfumato (smoky blending, da Vinci), and humanistic themes. Patronage shifted from church to wealthy merchants (Medici).",
